  "body": "i stumbled upon this code while writing slasher db store functions:\r\n`\treturn k.db.Batch(func(tx *bolt.Tx) error {\r\n\t\tbkt := tx.Bucket(attestationsBucket)\r\n\t\tfor i := 0; i < len(atts); i++ {\r\n\t\t\tindicesByBucket := createAttestationIndicesFromData(atts[i].Data, tx)\r\n\t\t\tif err := updateValueForIndices(indicesByBucket, keys[i], tx); err != nil {\r\n\t\t\t\treturn errors.Wrap(err, \"could not update DB indices\")\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\tif err := bkt.Put(keys[i], encodedValues[i]); err != nil {\r\n\t\t\t\treturn err\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t\treturn nil\r\n\t})\r\n}`\r\n\r\n[in SaveAttestations function ](https://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/blob/8f01b76366d0bfb17497f747fef47b96cb4bdbf4/beacon-chain/db/kv/attestations.go#L156-L169)\r\n\r\nfrom my experience with [boltdb batching](https://github.com/boltdb/bolt#batch-read-write-transactions) it doesn't work without calling it from separate goroutines\r\n\r\nto solve this issue we must call the put methods from separate goroutines.\r\n@rauljordan wdyt\r\n",
